<DOC><DOCNO> AP880705-0280 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-05-88 1428EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Columbia-Shell     07-05 0124</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Columbia-Shell,0130</SECOND><HEAD>Columbia Gas System Negotiating to Sell Partial Interest in LNGUnit</HEAD><DATELINE>WILMINGTON, Del. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Columbia Gas System Inc. announcedTuesday it is negotiating to sell a 50 percent interest in itssubsidiary, Columbia LNG Corp., to Shell Oil Co. of Houston.   Columbia said if the negotiations are successful, the partiesexpect to form a joint venture to purchase liquefied natural gassupplies and to market the LNG regasified at a terminal ColumbiaLNG owns at Cove Point, Md.   The terminal has the capacity to send out 1 billion cubic feetof gas daily.   Columbia said the terminal on the Chesapeake Bay is astrategically located entry point to major eastern energy marketsthrough its pipeline access to interstate transmission systems.</TEXT></DOC>